<p>These female refugees are invariably slatternly, dirty &amp; untidy, although some evidently have been used to other habits.  It is a pity to see bright intelligent looking kiddies gradually deteriorating under the bad influence.<br/>From Mont de Cats we followed a range of hills, then descended over the border in Belgium at the village of Boechepe.  Soon after leaving the village, which was crowded with lorries, &amp; which seemed to <strike>be</strike> contain at least three English Ambulance headquarters, we recrossed into France, &amp; came to the siding where the 3rd had established their headquarters &amp; were running a Rest Station</p>
